The Nigeria Labour Congress, NLC, has begun the two day rally, it promised, to register its displeasure over the lingering ASUU strike and other issues affecting the country. People talk took to the street to ask what people think about NLC and others who want to join the strike    NLC meets ASUU, others on solidarity rally In "News" The Nigeria labour congress (NLC) Kebbi state under the chairmanship of comrade Umar Halidu Alhassan on Tuesday held mass protest in Birnin Kebbi in complience with the National headquarters of the union In "News" The Nigeria Labour Congress, NLC, will today meet with leaders of the Academic Staff Union of Universities, ASUU, and others to put finishing touches to the planned solidarity rally the congress is organising in support of the ongoing strike by the university lecturers. In "Metro"